# Spec Writing Conventions

## Directory Structure

- `specs/product/features/<feature>.md` for user-facing purpose, current state, target state, and acceptance criteria
- `specs/implementation/<feature>.md` for repository-specific touch points, sequencing, and technical notes
- `specs/product/backlog/` for future ideas and proposals
- `specs/product/reference/` for domain explainers and supporting reference material
- `specs/design/README.md` for visual language, tokens, and UI guidance
- `specs/architecture/` for cross-cutting conventions and architecture notes
- `specs/milestones/<milestone>.md` for grouped deliverables and ordered checklists

## When Updating Specs

- Read the existing spec first and preserve accurate context.
- Keep product specs focused on behavior, goals, and acceptance criteria.
- Keep implementation specs focused on code touch points, sequencing, and constraints.
- Keep acceptance criteria concrete and testable.
- Put cross-cutting rules in `specs/architecture/` instead of repeating them in each feature spec.
